content.description: steep climbing up overhanging granite on big jugs. probably no move is harder than 10+ but the sustained nature pushes this climb and its sister into the easy 11 range. the right one is more sustained and consequently more enjoyable than its alluring sister to the left
content.protection: 12 bolts to a bolt and chain anchor
content.location: contour due west from start of Muttonhead south-side climbs (Mystery of the Desert, etc.) for approx. 200 feet. right bolted line. starts on small elevated platform
